Your sister mention me at all?

498
00:45:40,483 --> 00:45:41,677
Of course she does, right?

499
00:45:49,025 --> 00:45:52,085
Hey, Deusdete! What does
your sister say about me?

500
00:45:53,563 --> 00:45:55,224
She asks if you're okay.

501
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:58,794
That's all?

502
00:46:00,837 --> 00:46:02,236
What do you think?

503
00:46:03,139 --> 00:46:06,666
If she knew what you've been up to,
she wouldn't even be asking that.

504
00:46:08,545 --> 00:46:10,274
I think she would...

505
00:46:11,481 --> 00:46:13,472
...but you think you know better.

506
00:46:14,818 --> 00:46:18,185
Wasn't it you who used to say,
"If you sell it, don't use it"?

507
00:46:18,421 --> 00:46:19,581
Wasn't it you?

508
00:46:22,492 --> 00:46:23,720
May I?

509
00:46:23,993 --> 00:46:25,221
So, what's up?

510
00:46:27,230 --> 00:46:29,061
Come to settle your debt?

511
00:46:29,399 --> 00:46:32,994
Hey, man, right now Ezequiel's
in a tight spot.

512
00:46:33,336 --> 00:46:36,237
So he thinks to himself,
"Zico's a reasonable guy.

513
00:46:36,539 --> 00:46:39,303
He'll take the surfboard
as collateral for the debt."

514
00:46:40,510 --> 00:46:43,877
Then Ezequiel can have another
little rock of crack, right, man?

515
00:46:45,081 --> 00:46:46,514
Wrong.

516
00:46:53,923 --> 00:46:56,187
Pay what you owe!

517
00:47:01,498 --> 00:47:03,591
Don't drink that, it's blood!

518
00:47:06,636 --> 00:47:07,830
Shit!

519
00:47:09,339 --> 00:47:11,068
I thought it was water.

520
00:47:11,241 --> 00:47:15,302
Doctor, this guy was
sweating all night long.

521
00:47:15,478 --> 00:47:18,276
I've put him on antibiotics,
but if you ask me, it's no use.

522
00:47:18,448 --> 00:47:19,574
It's AIDS.

523
00:47:22,785 --> 00:47:24,150
Doctor!

524
00:47:26,022 --> 00:47:27,887
Who took away his oxygen?

525
00:47:30,793 --> 00:47:32,488
I don't want to die.

526
00:47:33,329 --> 00:47:37,026
Get me out of here, please!

527
00:47:38,668 --> 00:47:42,832
That's hardly likely.
He's 213. Rape.

528
00:47:43,506 --> 00:47:45,531
To us he's a patient.

529
00:47:49,679 --> 00:47:52,443
I can't...

530
00:47:52,615 --> 00:47:54,446
I need...

531
00:47:54,617 --> 00:47:56,608
...to get somewhere safe.

532
00:47:57,086 --> 00:47:59,987
- I don't want to die!
- I'm sorry, doctor.

533
00:48:00,156 --> 00:48:04,820
I'm against the death penalty,
but not for rape.

534
00:48:04,994 --> 00:48:07,189
If you ask me, it's just too bad.

535
00:48:14,237 --> 00:48:15,465
So that's it, doctor.

536
00:48:55,078 --> 00:48:57,706
Come on, old man. It's past lockdown.

537
00:49:19,702 --> 00:49:21,192
Get a move on!

538
00:49:28,945 --> 00:49:31,140
What is it? What are you looking at?

539
00:49:32,382 --> 00:49:35,317
You think your kids
will jump over the wall?

540
00:49:57,650 --> 00:49:59,743
You were asking for it this time,
weren't you?

541
00:50:05,725 --> 00:50:07,750
See you in 30 days.

542
00:50:16,602 --> 00:50:20,163
Doctor, we're here to make
our relationship official.

543
00:50:20,339 --> 00:50:22,398
With all due respect.

544
00:50:22,575 --> 00:50:26,944
You understand, doctor.
So we can be more open.

545
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:29,578
It's not the same with a rubber.

546
00:50:30,183 --> 00:50:33,710
There's not much sense,
her taking the test and not you.

547
00:50:34,053 --> 00:50:37,648
See? I told him, doctor,
but he's scared.

548
00:50:38,157 --> 00:50:39,454
Scared of what?

549
00:50:40,426 --> 00:50:43,156
- Scared of injections.
- Too Bad!

550
00:50:43,429 --> 00:50:46,421
- It's not that.
- So you're scared of getting married!

551
00:50:46,799 --> 00:50:47,166
Doctor, you're needed, urgently!

552
00:50:47,166 --> 00:50:49,396
Doctor, you're needed, urgently!

553
00:50:49,569 --> 00:50:50,558
Come on!

554
00:50:50,736 --> 00:50:52,601
Down you go, come on!

555
00:50:53,372 --> 00:50:54,896
It's all right now, doctor.

556
00:50:57,410 --> 00:50:58,934
I blacked out, doctor.

557
00:51:00,780 --> 00:51:02,577
Giving us all a fright, Zico?

558
00:51:04,016 --> 00:51:07,383
It's just as well, doctor.
Maybe he'll learn what drugs do.

559
00:51:07,653 --> 00:51:08,813
Tell him!

560
00:51:09,055 --> 00:51:11,580
What's there to tell? Drugs kill.

561
00:51:12,692 --> 00:51:14,887
- And you, who are you?
- That's Deusdete.

562
00:51:15,928 --> 00:51:17,919
We grew up together.

563
00:51:19,966 --> 00:51:21,365
You know, doctor...

564
00:51:22,001 --> 00:51:24,265
...one day my mother
didn't come home.

565
00:51:24,737 --> 00:51:26,170
I was left alone.

566
00:51:26,706 --> 00:51:27,764
I waited...

567
00:51:28,674 --> 00:51:29,936
...and waited...

568
00:51:31,878 --> 00:51:37,111
...until he and his sister, Franci,
came and took me to live with them.

569
00:51:47,426 --> 00:51:48,859
We grew up together.

570
00:51:51,898 --> 00:51:54,560
Wait!

571
00:52:16,522 --> 00:52:17,853
Come on, Zico!

572
00:52:33,005 --> 00:52:34,905
Wait, Zico!

573
00:53:01,934 --> 00:53:03,424
Zico!

574
00:53:06,939 --> 00:53:08,065
Help!

575
00:53:41,774 --> 00:53:43,537
Zico saved me, doctor.

576
00:53:44,810 --> 00:53:49,076
That's right. I've always
looked after him, from early on.

577
00:53:50,583 --> 00:53:53,416
Then you went the wrong way.

578
00:53:57,390 --> 00:54:02,828
What's wrong with buying some dope
and selling it to folks who like it?

579
00:54:03,896 --> 00:54:06,865
It wasn't even that much!
Another two years and I'm free.

580
00:54:07,300 --> 00:54:09,825
But I've never killed anyone.

581
00:54:11,137 --> 00:54:12,866
Unlike Deusdete here.

582
00:54:13,839 --> 00:54:15,568
What was your crime?

583
00:54:16,108 --> 00:54:17,769
Answer him, Deusdete!

584
00:54:23,149 --> 00:54:26,949
To tell you the truth,
he's not even a real criminal.

585
00:54:29,088 --> 00:54:31,113
So, what are you in here for?

586
00:54:32,958 --> 00:54:36,223
One night, I was at home...

587
00:54:37,196 --> 00:54:39,221
...when my sister arrived,
acting strange.

588
00:54:40,333 --> 00:54:41,630
Franci!

589
00:54:42,068 --> 00:54:44,969
What's wrong, Franci?
What happened?

590
00:54:45,171 --> 00:54:46,604
Franci!

591
00:54:54,280 --> 00:54:56,441
Franci, what happened?

592
00:54:58,250 --> 00:54:59,512
Open up, come on.

593
00:55:00,119 --> 00:55:02,053
What happened?

594
00:55:09,829 --> 00:55:11,387
What happened, Franci?

595
00:55:15,234 --> 00:55:17,464
What happened? Tell me.

596
00:55:18,471 --> 00:55:20,598
What happened?

597
00:55:23,576 --> 00:55:24,770
Tell me!

598
00:55:25,845 --> 00:55:27,642
There were two of them...

599
00:55:29,949 --> 00:55:31,382
...they grabbed me...

600
00:55:33,486 --> 00:55:35,317
...lifted my skirt.

601
00:55:38,290 --> 00:55:40,383
One said he wanted to suck me.

602
00:55:41,127 --> 00:55:44,494
- I told him to go suck his mother!
- What did they do to you?

603
00:55:44,663 --> 00:55:46,392
- They beat me.
- What else?

604
00:55:48,334 --> 00:55:49,392
What else?

605
00:55:49,568 --> 00:55:51,365
- That's all, Deusdete.
- Who was it?

606
00:55:51,537 --> 00:55:52,526
Who was it?

607
00:55:52,705 --> 00:55:55,469
- I just ran off!
- Did you know them?

608
00:56:04,383 --> 00:56:05,475
Hey, Zico!

609
00:56:08,988 --> 00:56:10,387
Deusdete?

610
00:56:10,656 --> 00:56:12,783
What are you doing here, man?

611
00:56:13,392 --> 00:56:14,859
I need to talk.

612
00:56:30,643 --> 00:56:32,235
Is Mother all right?

613
00:56:32,511 --> 00:56:34,411
It's not her.

614
00:56:35,080 --> 00:56:36,911
Some guys messed with Franci.

615
00:56:48,794 --> 00:56:50,261
What did they do to her?

616
00:56:51,163 --> 00:56:54,929
Nothing much, she says.
But I reported it to the cops anyway.

617
00:56:55,234 --> 00:56:59,068
The cops?! You think the cops
will do anything?!

618
00:56:59,238 --> 00:57:02,401
The problem is, the guys found out
and now they're after me.

619
00:57:06,479 --> 00:57:10,438
- Leave it to me. I'll sort them out.
- No, Zico. Not your way.

620
00:57:11,016 --> 00:57:12,210
I want...

621
00:57:16,222 --> 00:57:18,952
I just want a gun, to defend myself.

622
00:57:29,468 --> 00:57:30,867
Take your pick.

623
00:57:44,950 --> 00:57:47,976
Even with a gun, doctor, I never
thought anything would happen.

624
00:57:50,422 --> 00:57:56,258
But it was my destiny,
and theirs, when they found me.

625
00:58:04,770 --> 00:58:05,759
So!

626
00:58:06,772 --> 00:58:09,832
- Where's the stool pigeon off to?
- I'm not looking for a fight.

627
00:58:10,009 --> 00:58:12,876
- Let me go home.
- Sure thing...

628
00:58:13,145 --> 00:58:15,705
...but first we're going to caress you...

629
00:58:15,881 --> 00:58:18,179
...just like we did your little sister.

630
00:59:56,382 --> 00:59:57,610
Hey, man!

631
01:00:31,583 --> 01:00:33,244
Give me a Coke.

632
01:00:39,091 --> 01:00:41,685
You know how old I'll be
when I get out of here, doctor?

633
01:00:44,930 --> 01:00:46,420
Forty-eight.

634
01:00:48,233 --> 01:00:49,825
There!

635
01:00:55,607 --> 01:00:56,869
One...

636
01:00:58,010 --> 01:00:59,375
...two...

637
01:01:00,913 --> 01:01:02,073
...three...

638
01:01:03,382 --> 01:01:04,644
...four...

639
01:01:05,851 --> 01:01:07,341
...five...

640
01:01:08,087 --> 01:01:09,384
...six...

641
01:01:10,456 --> 01:01:11,821
...seven...

642
01:01:15,060 --> 01:01:16,459
...eight.

643
01:01:23,535 --> 01:01:25,093
Found it.

644
01:01:39,294 --> 01:01:40,886
So it's Visitors Day, is it?

645
01:01:42,497 --> 01:01:43,794
If you like...

646
01:01:44,165 --> 01:01:45,598
...you can go now.

647
01:01:58,847 --> 01:02:01,441
I've got a problem, I need to talk.

648
01:02:02,684 --> 01:02:04,515
This problem got a name?

649
01:02:05,053 --> 01:02:06,315
Ezequiel.

650
01:02:06,788 --> 01:02:09,814
He still owes me and now he's
trying to get more on account.

651
01:02:10,959 --> 01:02:14,417
He comes to my cell, raises his voice.
What's he playing at?

652
01:02:14,929 --> 01:02:16,920
- And you?
- Me?

653
01:02:17,699 --> 01:02:20,395
If I don't get paid,
I can't pay Highness.

654
01:02:21,503 --> 01:02:24,063
I want your permission
to kill the bastard.

655
01:02:24,405 --> 01:02:27,863
This goes on much longer,
I'll start losing respect around here.

656
01:02:28,042 --> 01:02:29,532
Cool it.

657
01:02:30,945 --> 01:02:34,437
I'll tell Ezequiel to get
the money from his family.

658
01:02:35,049 --> 01:02:38,985
If he doesn't pay,
you can go ahead.

659
01:02:49,330 --> 01:02:51,628
This man has already lost a lung...

660
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:55,930
...and the other's in pretty bad shape.
- Take the medicine, man, go on.

661
01:02:57,772 --> 01:03:00,036
See, doctor? He won't take it.

662
01:03:01,309 --> 01:03:03,277
What are you, a kid?
You won't get better...

663
01:03:03,444 --> 01:03:06,845
...if you don't take it.
- Come on, that's right.

664
01:03:08,483 --> 01:03:09,507
That's it.

665
01:03:14,889 --> 01:03:15,878
Come on.

666
01:03:17,559 --> 01:03:18,617
Right.

667
01:03:23,097 --> 01:03:26,294
- Good.
- And on the outside? What did he do?

668
01:03:26,601 --> 01:03:28,831
We used to rob armored trucks.

669
01:03:29,003 --> 01:03:33,201
Just the two of us.
We planned everything. Remember?

670
01:03:33,474 --> 01:03:36,602
Doctor, we'd spend six months
just gathering information.

671
01:03:36,778 --> 01:03:39,144
We'd even make friends
with the guards' families.

672
01:03:39,314 --> 01:03:40,781
And that paid off?

673
01:03:41,115 --> 01:03:45,074
Sure, plenty. Although
we'd only use half the money.

674
01:03:45,320 --> 01:03:49,586
The rest we'd put aside
for a rainy day...

675
01:03:49,824 --> 01:03:51,917
...or to bribe the cops.

676
01:04:05,640 --> 01:04:06,800
It's coming.

677
01:04:38,039 --> 01:04:39,472
Stop!

678
01:04:41,910 --> 01:04:45,038
You going to sit there
on top of other people's money?

679
01:04:45,213 --> 01:04:47,841
If you don't come out it'll be
too bad for your widows.

680
01:04:48,016 --> 01:04:49,745
Open that door,
for Christ's sake!

681
01:04:52,120 --> 01:04:53,678
Come on, get out!

682
01:04:53,922 --> 01:04:56,356
So we paid off the others...

683
01:04:56,524 --> 01:04:59,516
...and each went his own way
back to the family.

684
01:05:01,763 --> 01:05:04,197
So anyway, Antônio,
what's on your mind?

685
01:05:07,535 --> 01:05:08,763
Miro...

686
01:05:10,305 --> 01:05:12,398
...your wife's cheating on you.

687
01:05:13,775 --> 01:05:15,242
With a cop.

688
01:05:18,780 --> 01:05:21,772
- Says who?
- Says no one. I saw her.

689
01:05:22,083 --> 01:05:25,280
They were making out in a squad car.

690
01:05:26,421 --> 01:05:28,389
Near the old bakery.

691
01:05:38,299 --> 01:05:40,130
Dina doesn't buy bread there.

692
01:05:40,301 --> 01:05:43,668
Miro, I saw her.
And it wasn't bread she was after.

693
01:05:52,125 --> 01:05:53,387
Célia...

694
01:05:54,961 --> 01:05:57,020
...is Antônio Carlos gay?

695
01:05:58,432 --> 01:06:00,297
What a question, Dina!

696
01:06:03,103 --> 01:06:07,972
He made up this story and told Miro
I've been going out with a cop.

697
01:06:08,141 --> 01:06:12,373
Like hell I made it up.
I saw you crawling all over him.

698
01:06:12,546 --> 01:06:17,245
- You nibbled his ear, damn it!
- Then it's me he's really after.

699
01:06:18,018 --> 01:06:20,714
You forgot the best part...

700
01:06:20,987 --> 01:06:24,286
...how you asked me to run away
with you...

701
01:06:24,458 --> 01:06:26,016
...and that I turned you down...

702
01:06:26,193 --> 01:06:28,024
...because I love my husband...

703
01:06:28,362 --> 01:06:30,193
...and your wife's my friend.

704
01:06:31,264 --> 01:06:32,731
Liar!

705
01:06:32,999 --> 01:06:34,660
Evil slut!

706
01:06:42,669 --> 01:06:47,129
Miro, you don't believe that bitch,
do you?

707
01:06:49,343 --> 01:06:53,074
Man, how many jobs have we
pulled off together?

708
01:06:54,448 --> 01:06:56,848
And our agreement!

709
01:06:57,017 --> 01:07:00,453
Célia, see if you can keep your man
around the house.

710
01:07:00,621 --> 01:07:03,351
I don't want him pestering me
in the street anymore.

711
01:07:06,860 --> 01:07:08,122
Miro!

712
01:07:13,267 --> 01:07:15,667
- Miro!
- Bastard! You dirty bastard!

713
01:07:16,003 --> 01:07:17,368
You've never fooled me.

714
01:07:17,537 --> 01:07:20,097
I always knew you had a crush on her.

715
01:07:20,274 --> 01:07:23,471
You can't even respect your
best friend's wife, you dog!

716
01:07:23,644 --> 01:07:25,544
- Calm down.
- Dog!

717
01:07:30,150 --> 01:07:33,415
Miro, I'm telling you the truth!

718
01:07:41,295 --> 01:07:43,229
I lost my friend and partner.

719
01:07:43,597 --> 01:07:46,896
The first robbery without him,
there were so many cops...

720
01:07:47,067 --> 01:07:49,399
...it looked more like a military parade.

721
01:07:49,703 --> 01:07:52,934
- What about him?
- I only found out when he got here.

722
01:07:53,307 --> 01:07:55,935
I thought I'd gone to hell, doctor.

723
01:07:56,109 --> 01:07:57,701
But him? I'll tell you.

724
01:07:58,178 --> 01:07:59,668
Come here, come on.

725
01:08:00,013 --> 01:08:01,480
Come on.

726
01:08:19,232 --> 01:08:20,221
Miro.

727
01:08:21,368 --> 01:08:23,529
Miro, don't you think it's time you quit?

728
01:08:26,239 --> 01:08:29,572
Take what you've got and start
a decent life someplace else?

729
01:08:29,743 --> 01:08:31,210
In a new city?

730
01:08:31,545 --> 01:08:35,276
Give the kid a better chance?

731
01:09:02,242 --> 01:09:03,709
Stop! Police!

732
01:09:05,445 --> 01:09:07,276
Party's over, Miro.

733
01:09:08,382 --> 01:09:10,009
I'll cut you in.

734
01:09:10,384 --> 01:09:14,684
It's cheaper for me to cut you guys in
than give it to a lawyer.

735
01:09:14,855 --> 01:09:16,083
You don't get it.

736
01:09:16,256 --> 01:09:18,690
We're taking the lot. Everything.

737
01:09:18,859 --> 01:09:20,724
Hand it over, the dough.
Come on, quick.

738
01:09:34,041 --> 01:09:38,205
Too bad, a smart guy like you
trusting his own wife.

739
01:09:38,879 --> 01:09:41,404
Some guys are born
to be cheated on.

740
01:09:57,998 --> 01:09:59,329
Are you all right?

741
01:10:21,689 --> 01:10:22,986
Doctor...

742
01:10:25,025 --> 01:10:31,362
...do infants remember
everything we do?

743
01:10:33,067 --> 01:10:36,093
No, not a thing.

744
01:10:38,339 --> 01:10:41,240
Doctor, let him go.

745
01:11:11,472 --> 01:11:13,099
And with you now...

746
01:11:13,274 --> 01:11:16,641
...our untamed diva of dance...

747
01:11:16,911 --> 01:11:20,142
...the woman who lives in all
thieves' hearts...

748
01:11:20,314 --> 01:11:25,274
...here at the detention center...

749
01:11:25,452 --> 01:11:30,822
...the one and only Rita Cadillac!

750
01:11:33,294 --> 01:11:35,762
- Rita!
- Rita!

751
01:12:23,577 --> 01:12:24,669
Hello!

752
01:12:25,646 --> 01:12:27,910
I know you all...

753
01:12:28,449 --> 01:12:32,180
...fool around a lot, right?

754
01:12:32,486 --> 01:12:33,976
Yes!

755
01:12:34,989 --> 01:12:37,549
But do you take care
of yourselves?

756
01:12:37,925 --> 01:12:39,256
